column1: 'The First Lady' is a harsh reminder of this truth
column2: "Women are like teabags. You never know how strong they are until you put them in hot water." And near the end of the first episode, she offers a pithy summary of her own position. Pressed by an aide to attend a meeting because it is her job as First Lady, Roosevelt shoots back, "That's not a job. That's my circumstance."
